The paper deals with recommender systems (RSs) and proposes a new method for computing similarities between users and items in a Heterogeneous Information Network (HIN). This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Databases (cs.DB), and possibly Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) if the focus is on user experience. Among these, cs.IR and cs.SI seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with recommendation algorithms and network analysis.
